id: pm-4a7m
title: "Promote history-stream maintenance primitives to the public SDK: history-redact, history-repair, history-compact (audited rewrite, re-anchor, checkpoint/prune)"
description: "The existing promotion set (pm-98cz lifecycle, pm-rjqr reads, pm-zwpp facets, pm-oxrw governance, pm-3mna workspace config) leaves the history MUTATION family uncovered: history-redact (audited redaction), history-repair (chain re-anchor after drift), history-compact (checkpoint/prune preserving replay integrity), all built on the shared history-rewrite orchestration (dedup'd in closed pm-bzgt). SDK-first requires these as public typed primitives so the consolidated pm history subcommands (pm-tqel) become thin shims and integrators can run stream maintenance programmatically. Duplicate check: pm-tqel is the CLI-grammar counterpart; pm-xk39/pm-bzgt closed history; no open SDK-promotion overlap."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: architecture,"area:history","area:sdk"
created_at: "2026-07-05T05:09:03.180Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T02:22:21.060Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T02:21:49.963Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "SDK exports typed redact/repair/compact primitives preserving audited-rewrite guarantees (hash chain continuity, replay integrity, checkpoint markers, redaction audit trail) and returning the same structured results the CLI prints; CLI history maintenance commands consume only these primitives; docstrings + linked tests + SDK reference docs; zero behavior change (history rewrite/compact/redact specs green)."
parent: pm-usfg
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: "Promoted audited redact, repair, checkpoint/prune compact, verified stream read/replay, and MCP adapters to public SDK modules; CLI history commands are presentation shims and PmClient exposes typed maintenance methods."
expected_result: Public SDK owns typed history maintenance primitives with audited rewrite and replay integrity while CLI behavior remains compatible.
actual_result: "Public history maintenance, runtime-input, and MCP adapter primitives now share canonical CLI usage-error semantics; invalid integer values and mutually exclusive compaction scopes return EXIT_CODE.USAGE. Full coverage passes 5657 tests at 100/100/100/100, and linked SDK/history/MCP verification passes."
