comments[9]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T22:45:34.851Z",codex-root,"Implementation evidence: maintenance domain ownership moved from three CLI command files into public SDK modules; CLI paths are compatibility shims; shared history read and verified replay kernels eliminate presentation-layer and duplicate patch replay dependencies. Focused 161-test matrix passed after extraction."
  "2026-07-14T00:09:45.639Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: promoted redact, repair, compact, verified stream read/replay, and MCP adapters into public SDK ownership; PmClient and top-level exports now share typed runtime input normalization. SDK private-import boundary ratcheted from 761 to 713. Exact-tree build, typecheck, lint, zero-clone duplication scan, static quality, package-boundary, token-budget, contracts, and secret scan all pass; full sandboxed coverage passes 5656 tests at 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T00:29:09.568Z",codex-root,"Final verification: full sandboxed coverage 5656/5656 at 100/100/100/100; strict build/type/lint/static/package-boundary/contracts/security gates pass; 88-command package-first dogfood passes; installed tarball SDK history/children and real compaction pass in /tmp/pm-cli-acceptance-Edurt3."
  "2026-07-14T01:57:21.245Z",codex-root,"Exact-head Greptile release review 6a3e334e-3311-4172-a7ba-ffba3a7d30c3 found a P1 SDK contract mismatch: parseRuntimeInteger hardcodes exit code 64 while pm validation errors use EXIT_CODE.USAGE=2. Reopened canonical runtime-input owner to replace the literal with the shared constant and assert number/string invalid-input exit codes."
  "2026-07-14T02:03:13.487Z",codex-root,"Review remediation evidence: replaced parseRuntimeInteger's hardcoded 64 with the shared EXIT_CODE.USAGE contract and added direct valid/string/number regression coverage. Focused 14-test SDK/MCP run, ESLint, 100% docstring/static/package/token gates, full 5657-test 100/100/100/100 coverage, and the sandboxed 35-test linked matrix all pass."
  "2026-07-14T02:03:52.538Z",codex-root,"Changelog closeout: pm-changelog installation advanced to latest available 2026.7.14; managed package metadata is retained and CHANGELOG.md regenerated from the final closed tracker state."
  "2026-07-14T02:17:36.908Z",codex-root,"Exact-head Greptile review 8540a350-c6b0-4354-8496-5fc1300c913c returned zero formal comments but identified an actionable summary inconsistency: runMcpHistoryCompactAction scope conflicts hardcode 64 while sibling parseRuntimeInteger failures use EXIT_CODE.USAGE=2. Reopened the same SDK history adapter owner before editing."
  "2026-07-14T02:21:49.165Z",codex-root,"Second review remediation evidence: the MCP history-compact scope-conflict branch now uses EXIT_CODE.USAGE and its integration assertion verifies both message and exit code. Focused 14-test run, ESLint, strict static/docstring/package/token gates, and full 5657-test coverage at 100/100/100/100 pass."
  "2026-07-14T02:22:21.059Z",codex-root,"Final changelog package refresh: latest registry version advanced to pm-changelog 2026.7.14-1; managed metadata and the unchanged generated CHANGELOG are verified at the final closed tracker state."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T17:46:11.520Z",maintainer-agent,"Promotion slicing S1-S4 (pass #53 code survey). Territory = history-redact.ts 783 + history-compact.ts 759 + history-repair.ts 428 lines; ALL domain logic (rule parsing, rewrite, replay, re-anchor, rollback) lives in CLI command files; SDK exports none of it. Blockers pm-lodl/pm-muhw closed - actionable now.\nDuplication evidence: applyHistoryPatch is implemented TWICE (history-redact.ts:313 and history-compact.ts:169) inside command files while core/history/replay.ts exists - promotion consolidates into one kernel.\nS1 redaction engine (~90m): move buildRedactionRules / applyLiteralRule / applyRegexRule / redactUnknownValue / rewriteHistoryEntries / inspectHistoryIntegrity + apply/rollback into core/history/redaction.ts; SDK exports redactHistory() returning the audit-trail result (rules applied, replacement counts, integrity snapshot).\nS2 repair primitive (~45m): history-repair.ts (428 lines, 6 fns) becomes repairHistory() re-anchor primitive taking a drift report from scanHistoryDrift.\nS3 compact primitive (~75m): parseBeforeBoundary / replayHistoryAndResolveCheckpoint / reanchorRetainedEntries / apply-rewrite become compactHistory() checkpoint/prune primitive; core/history/history-compact-bulk.ts is already core-side - align with it.\nS4 shared integrity kernel (~60m): one replay + hash-chain verification module consumed by all three primitives AND by the immutability consumers pm-3z0k (attestation) and pm-hib1 (get --at) - same kernel, multiple call sites; replay-integrity spec matrix + SDK reference docs.\nRecommended entry: S1 (largest file, fully self-contained pure functions); fold the kernel extraction into whichever of S1/S3 lands first."
